cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically with light field synthesis, parallax correction, and occlusion completion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics and rendering techniques, which could fall under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of a generative-adversarial network model suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
